==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Crucifix
<hw>Cru"ci*fix</hw> <pr>(kr?"s?-f?ks)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Crucifixes</plw> <pr>(-<?/z)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[F.
<ets>crucifix or LL</ets>. <ets>crucifixum</ets>, fr. L.
<ets>crux</ets>, <ets>crucis</ets>, cross + <ets>figere</ets>,
<ets>fixum</ets>, to fix. See <er>Cross</er>, and <er>Fix</er>, and cf.
Crucify.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A representation in art of the figure
of Christ upon the cross; esp., the sculptured figure affixed to a real
cross of wood, ivory, metal, or the like, used by the Roman Catholics in
their devotions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The cross, too, by degrees, become the <qex>crucifix</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And kissing oft her <qex>crucifix</qex>,⟦br⟧
Unto the block she drew.</q> <rj><qau>Warner.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The cross or religion of Christ.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Jer. Taylor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crucifixion</ent>⟦br⟧
